<BaseLayout
  title="PH Gaming Intel — Philippines Gaming Industry News & Analysis"
  description="PH Gaming Intel covers the Philippines gaming industry with in-depth news, regulatory analysis, PAGCOR updates, POGO tracking, and IR resort coverage."
  activePage="news"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>

  <!-- HERO — Featured Story -->
  <section class="hero-featured" aria-label="Featured story">
    <img src="/hero/pasay-to-sihanoukville-worker-migration.png"
         alt="A POGO worker's migration from Pasay to Sihanoukville — layered map and silhouettes"
         width="1920" height="1080" loading="eager">
    <div class="overlay">
      <div class="overlay-inner">
        <span class="tag tag-longread">Longread</span>
        <h1>From Pasay to Sihanoukville: A POGO Worker's Migration</h1>
        <p class="dek">When the Philippine offshore gaming industry was shut down in 2024, the buildings emptied. The workers had to go somewhere. A reconstructed account of one path — and what the journey reveals about a regional labor market in transition.</p>
        <p class="meta">May 27, 2026 &middot; 22 min read &middot; Editorial Score 10/10</p>
        <a href="/articles/pasay-to-sihanoukville-worker-migration.html" style="display:inline-block;margin-top:16px;padding:12px 28px;border-radius:8px;background:var(--gold);color:var(--dark);font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:14px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.5px;transition:background .2s;">Read the Full Story</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- LATEST NEWS -->
  <section class="mt-section mb-section" id="latest-news" aria-label="Latest news">
    <div class="section-wrap">
      <h2 class="section-title">Latest News</h2>
      <div class="card-grid">

        <a href="/articles/world-cup-2026-france-sole-favorite-mbappe-short-odds-philippines" class="card">
          <div class="card-img">
            <img src="/hero/world-cup-2026-france-sole-favorite-mbappe-short-odds-philippines.png"
                 alt="A wide field of odds-columns collapsing inward toward a single short, tall column as smaller columns fade at the edges"
                 width="640" height="360" loading="lazy">
          </div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <span class="tag tag-news">News</span>
            <h3>France Alone at +400: What a Shrinking Favorite Does to a Betting Board — and to the People Reading It</h3>
            <p class="card-dek">Mbappé's brace against Senegal made him France's all-time top scorer and pushed France to the front of the board as the sole favorite at ~+400 — its shortest since December. No tips, no picks: why a short favorite is "more likely" but not "better value," how the house margin bites hardest on thin payouts, and the parlay trap a heavy favorite is designed to set.</p>
            <p class="card-meta">June 18, 2026 &middot; Score 9/10</p>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a href="/articles/world-cup-2026-opening-week-goals-glut-over-under-philippines" class="card">
          <div class="card-img">
            <img src="/hero/world-cup-2026-opening-week-goals-glut-over-under-philippines.png"
                 alt="A rising tide of small goal-arc forms lifting a horizontal threshold line, with a balance scale tipping above it"
                 width="640" height="360" loading="lazy">
          </div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <span class="tag tag-news">News</span>
            <h3>England 4-2, Hat Tricks and Braces: When a Goal-Soaked Opening Week Bends the Over/Under Board</h3>
            <p class="card-dek">The tournament opened with a flood of goals — and with it, the most contagious bet on the board: the Over. How totals lines are priced, why a -110 "coin flip" actually needs 52.4% to break even, why books raise the line after a goal-glut, and why "this is a high-scoring World Cup" is a small-sample feeling history tends to reverse.</p>
            <p class="card-meta">June 18, 2026 &middot; Score 9/10</p>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a href="/articles/world-cup-2026-mexico-south-korea-late-night-live-betting-philippines" class="card">
          <div class="card-img">
            <img src="/hero/world-cup-2026-mexico-south-korea-late-night-live-betting-philippines.png"
                 alt="A clock face dissolving into a stream of fast in-play bet-tiles under a low moon, a single calm guard-rail line cutting across"
                 width="640" height="360" loading="lazy">
          </div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <span class="tag tag-news">News</span>
            <h3>Mexico v South Korea at 3 a.m.: The World Cup's North American Kickoffs Are a Live-Betting Risk Window for Filipinos</h3>
            <p class="card-dek">A marquee Asian-interest fixture lands deep in the Philippine overnight hours — and the tournament's late kickoffs collide with the one product built to exploit a tired, alone, late-night decision: live, in-play betting. Why the overnight window is the riskiest of the tournament, how in-play is engineered for speed over reflection, and the guardrails that actually help.</p>
            <p class="card-meta">June 18, 2026 &middot; Score 9/10</p>
          </div>
        </a>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

